## Auto Behaviors

> These rules apply automatically in every session. No explicit trigger needed.

### Task Type Detection

| Signal | Task Type | Auto Action |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| docs/, .plan, PRD, architecture, planning mentioned | **Planning Mode** | Run Planning Protocol |
| source code file modifications | **Coding Mode** | Run Coding Protocol |
| "check", "review", "look at", diff, compare | **Review Mode** | Run Review Protocol |
| "done", "finished", "wrap up", "commit" | **Wrap Mode** | Run Wrap Protocol |
| WebSearch, WebFetch, Context7 query-docs executed | **Research Mode** | Run Research Protocol |

### Planning Protocol
```
1. Read `docs/PROJECT_TODO.md` Phase Dashboard -> find active phase
2. Read active phase file `docs/phases/{prefix}` -> check task status
3. Check consistency with existing documentation
4. Present list of affected documents if changes are made
5. Log planning changes in PROJECT_TODO.md Work Log
```

### Coding Protocol
```
1. Read LESSONS.md to recall mistake patterns (once per session, on first coding task)
2. Read target files before modifying (no guessing)
3. Check if related test files exist
4. Run typecheck after modifying typed code
5. Report changed file list and summary to user
6. Run tests if they exist and report results
```

### Review Protocol
```
1. Check git diff of target files
2. Summarize changes (what changed and why)
3. Identify affected files/services
4. Check for potential issues (N+1, unused variables, hardcoded values, etc.)
5. Check test coverage
```

### Wrap Protocol
```
1. List all changed files
2. git add + commit (after user confirmation)
3. Update active phase file:
   - Completed items: - [ ] -> - [x] + Completed: YYYY-MM-DD
   - Update Progress Summary table
4. Update PROJECT_TODO.md:
   - Increment Phase Dashboard Done count
   - Add today's work to Work Log
5. Add new lessons to LESSONS.md if applicable
```

### Document Link Protocol (on doc rename/restructure/cross-reference)
```
1. If ADDING a cross-reference link to another doc:
   - Add backlink entry in target doc's ## Backlinks table
   - Add forward + backlink rows in docs/LINK_REGISTRY.md
2. If RENAMING or MOVING a doc:
   - Check docs/LINK_REGISTRY.md for all backlinks to that doc
   - Update every referring document's link
3. If DELETING a doc:
   - Remove all references found via LINK_REGISTRY.md backlinks
   - Remove entry from LINK_REGISTRY.md
4. Run validation: node scripts/check-doc-links.js
```

### Research Protocol (after any external lookup)
```
1. After WebSearch / WebFetch / Context7 query-docs results received:
   - Create cache file: docs/research/{category}/{slug}.md (use TEMPLATE.md format)
   - Categories: searches/ (WebSearch), apis/ (WebFetch), libraries/ (Context7)
   - Update index: Add row to docs/research/00_INDEX.md
   - If not worth caching: Add SKIP row to index with reason
2. Hook enforcement: next tool call is BLOCKED until cache or SKIP is completed
3. resolve-library-id is exempt (ID lookup only, no content)
4. State auto-expires after 2 hours
```

### Git Protocol (always on commit)
```
1. Check changed files with git status
2. Generate conventional commit message (feat/fix/docs/refactor/style/test/chore)
3. Show commit message to user and get confirmation
4. Add dated entry to Work Log section in docs/PROJECT_TODO.md (index)
```

### No Unilateral Completion
- **Only the user decides if a task is complete.** Claude never marks tasks done on its own.
- Changing `- [ ]` -> `- [x]` in phase files is only allowed after user says "done", "finished", "complete".
- When you believe work is done: report "Work completed. Please confirm." and wait.

